{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"76cfbc49-aab1-4dcd-9390-2fbc78e18566","content":"With Microsoft.Testing.Platform the switches change and everything goes after `--`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Mapping:**\n\n| VSTest flag | MTP equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--collect-coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to the test project):\n\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild` — enables `dotnet test` integration\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` — for `--report-trx`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` — for `--collect-coverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` — for `--crashdump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` — for `--hangdump`","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"79eb13d9-10fc-44fd-98e8-0b026616fd7f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure, not a codebase task.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nKey differences:\n- `--filter` → `--filter`(same)\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx`\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect-coverage` with `--coverage-output-format cobertura` (using Microsoft.CodeCoverage)\n\n\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n- `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nFor running with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, they can either use `dotnet run` or the test executable directly, but if they want to stick with `dotnet test`, they'll need to enable the new platform in their project file and use the updated flags. Starting with .NET 9 SDK, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nWith .NET 8, I need to clarify the approach: if they have the MSBuild integration package, they can still use `dotnet test` but the flags change, or they can run the test app directly. When using `dotnet test` with the Microsoft.Testing.Platform MSBuild integration, it acts as a wrapper and passes arguments after `--` directly to the platform. I'm mapping out how the Microsoft.Testing.Platform options translate from the old `dotnet test` syntax—`--filter` stays the same at the dotnet level, while platform-specific features like `--report-trx`, `--collect-coverage`, `--crashdump`, and `--hangdump` go after the `--` separator and require their respective extension packages.","outputTokens":1458},"id":"439737ba-cd9e-479b-8c0d-de26dcfe6205","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:22:42.384Z","parentId":"31bd4b53-e4bc-47c0-8204-5362cd797ecf"}
